<item>
  <title>MonksHillLabs Initiative</title>
  <link>https://DaMIfLL.github.io/projects/monkshilllabs.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>MonksHillLabs is a collaborative research platform that provides shared computational infrastructure, data repositories, and development environments for landscape and land use modelling projects.</p>
<p>The initiative brings together researchers, data scientists, and software developers to co-create tools, standards, and workflows that advance data interoperability and reproducible research in landscape science.</p>
<p>Current activities include developing standardized data formats, building modular modelling components, and hosting hackathons and training workshops.</p>



 ]]></description>
  <category>infrastructure</category>
  <category>collaboration</category>
  <category>research platform</category>
  <guid>https://DaMIfLL.github.io/projects/monkshilllabs.html</guid>
  <pubDate>Thu, 14 Nov 2024 23:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
</item>
<item>
  <title>Living Lab Dashboards</title>
  <link>https://DaMIfLL.github.io/projects/living-lab-dashboards.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>The Living Lab Dashboards project develops interactive web-based tools for visualizing and exploring data from living lab experiments conducted across our research network.</p>
<p>These dashboards integrate diverse data streams including environmental sensors, field observations, and remote sensing data to provide real-time insights into landscape dynamics and experimental outcomes.</p>
<p>The platform supports collaborative analysis and data-driven decision making for adaptive management of living lab sites.</p>



 ]]></description>
  <category>dashboard</category>
  <category>visualization</category>
  <category>living labs</category>
  <guid>https://DaMIfLL.github.io/projects/living-lab-dashboards.html</guid>
  <pubDate>Sat, 31 Aug 2024 22:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
