<item>
  <title>Resources and tools</title>
  <link>https://DaMIfLL.github.io/resources.html</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>This repo is intended to be a living document for SWG and IAT members to share useful information and resources related to Open Science, programming and Data Visualisation.</p>
<p>Some documents that provide guiding principles:</p>
<ul>
<li><p><a href="https://zalf365.sharepoint.com/sites/dokumentencenter/Richtlinien/2023-01-richtlinie-zalf-data-policy.pdf?csf=1&amp;web=1&amp;e=irWOai">Handling Research Data at ZALF Guidelinbes</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://zalf365.sharepoint.com/sites/vorstand/Freigegebene%20Dokumente/strategiedokumente/policy-open-access.pdf?csf=1&amp;web=1&amp;e=4bXvat">ZALF open access policy</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://doi.org/10.20387/BonaRes-RYCV-30RK">BonaRes Data Policy</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://www.leibniz-gemeinschaft.de/ueber-uns/evaluierung/das-evaluierungsverfahren-der-leibniz-gemeinschaft/senatsstellungnahmen">Previous ZALF evaluations</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://zalf365.sharepoint.com/sites/vorstand/Freigegebene%20Dokumente/Forms/AllItems.aspx?id=%2Fsites%2Fvorstand%2FFreigegebene%20Dokumente%2Fstrategiedokumente%2Forganizational%2Dpolicy%2Dzalf%2Epdf&amp;parent=%2Fsites%2Fvorstand%2FFreigegebene%20Dokumente%2Fstrategiedokumente">ZALF organisational policy</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://www.dfg.de/de/grundlagen-themen/grundlagen-und-prinzipien-der-foerderung/gwp">DFG research ethics</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://www.leibniz-gemeinschaft.de/ueber-uns/leibniz-integritaet/gute-wissenschaftliche-praxis-und-ombudswesen">Liebniz center Good Scientific Practice</a></p></li>
</ul>
<p>Check out the <a href="https://github.com/awesomelistsio/awesome-open-science">Open Science Awesome List</a></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://book.the-turing-way.org/collaboration/new-community/new-community-guide/">The Turing Way’s Guide to Planning a Community</a> - A guide to planning and building a community around open science, including tips on communication, governance, and sustainability.</li>
</ul>
<section id="data-visualisation" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="data-visualisation">Data visualisation</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://clauswilke.com/dataviz/">Fundamentals of Data Visualization</a></li>
<li><a href="https://openvisualizationacademy.org/">Open Visualisation Academy</a></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="r" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="r">R</h2>
<p>What they forgot to teach you about R: https://rstats.wtf/</p>
</section>
<section id="quarto" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="quarto">Quarto</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://slidecrafting-book.com/">Beautiful slides with RevealJS and Quarto</a></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="tools-and-software" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="tools-and-software">Tools and Software</h2>
<ul>
<li><p><a href="https://european-alternatives.eu/categories">EU alternatives for software</a> - A directory of software alternatives to popular proprietary software, with a focus on European users and organizations.</p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://www.gettingstuffdone.ai/">gettingstuffdoneai</a> - Directory of Generative AI Tools and Models, categorized by use case and functionality.</p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://inkscape.org/">Inkscape</a> - Open source vector graphics editor, alternative to Adobe products, useful for creating and editing figures for publications and presentations. Available via the ZALF baramundi client.</p></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="training" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="training">Training</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://digital-research.academy/">Digital Research Academy</a> - a trainer network focused on Open Science, Data Literacy, and Research Software Engineering (DRA’s <a href="https://zenodo.org/communities/digiresacademy/records?q=&amp;l=list&amp;p=1&amp;s=10&amp;sort=newest">Zenodo collection</a>).</li>
<li><a href="https://www.berd-nfdi.de/berd-academy/">BERD academy</a></li>
<li><a href="https://berd-nfdi.github.io/BERD-reproducible-research-course/">BERD reproducible research course</a></li>
<li><a href="https://edutrain.nfdi4earth.de/">NFDI4Earth - Educational Portal</a></li>
<li><a href="https://assured-training.org/">Assured Training</a> -Ensures the safe, legal, and ethical use of sensitive data through targeted training and certification.</li>
<li><a href="https://ki-campus.org/en/learning-opportunities/courses">KI-campus</a> - Numerous free courses on AI and related topics, including data science, machine learning, and ethical considerations in AI.</li>
</ul>


</section>

 ]]></description>
  <guid>https://DaMIfLL.github.io/resources.html</guid>
  <pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 13:42:15 GMT</pubDate>
